[Accuracy and Reliability]
- All responses and generated code must prioritize referencing official documentation, standards, and well-verified libraries.
- Any uncertain or unverified information should be clearly indicated with disclaimers such as "verification required" or "subject to further confirmation."
- Avoid presenting speculative or unsupported answers as facts.
- Code examples must be testable, with an aim for at least 80% test coverage through unit and integration tests.
- Input validation and proper error handling are mandatory to ensure stability and correctness.

[Documentation]
- Comprehensive comments and documentation are required for all APIs, functions, and modules.
- JSDoc-style comments should be included to improve code readability and maintainability.

[Security]
- Generated code must avoid hardcoding sensitive information such as passwords or API keys.
- Authentication and authorization checks should be included wherever applicable.
- Follow current best security practices including data encryption and secure handling of credentials.

[Language]
- All AI-generated outputs, including responses and code comments, must be written in Korean to ensure consistency and clarity.

[Feedback and Improvement]
- Promptly incorporate feedback and corrections into subsequent iterations.
- Clearly indicate when updates or revisions are recommended.

[Rule Language]
- All rules and guidelines must be followed based on the English version.
- In case of any ambiguity or conflict, the English rules take precedence over translations.
- Translations are provided for reference and clarity but do not override the English original.